                                         JOHANNESBURG - A taxi driver has been shot dead in Florida west of Joburg. Paramedics say the man was found lying on the side of the road along the Gordon and Hendrick Potgieter intersection. Spokesman Russel Meiring says the passengers escaped unharmed. “Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained several gunshot wounds which left him in a critical condition. CPR and advanced life support interventions were immediately initiated in an effort to revive the patient, unfortunately, after some time no life signs returned, and the man was declared dead at the scene.”